        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2020-02-27 02:39:16.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 6:\n\n(3 comments)\n\n> Patch Set 4:\n> \n> > > Patch Set 3:\n>  > >\n>  > > (1 comment)\n>  > \n>  > Thanks Liam, seems it is another issue than the one you mentioned.\n>  > It could be related to this one:\n>  > https://community.sonarsource.com/t/intellij-plugin-not-working-when-bound-to-sonarqube/17682\n>  > \n>  > IntelliJ I use is on JDK 11.\n> \n> Did this work?  \"Unsupported class file major version 55\" implies that IntelliJ, itself, was launched with an older version of Java (e.g., JDK8).  That happens with eclipse: besides changing the project and java build path to JDK11, you also have to change the eclipse launcher to use JDK11.  Maybe the same with IntelliJ?\n\nIt seems the opposite. I tried to let IntelliJ itself use JDK8, then the problem was gone. Maybe the SonarServer uses older JDK. \n\nFrom the above link:\nThe problem happens in connected mode, when the server version is older than the one embedded in SonarLint.",
